title: Camden Hills eighth, Mount View 10th at team states
text:
Camden Hills eighth, Mount View 10th at team states Windjammers Starbird, Anderson shoot 74, 75 respectively By Staff | Oct 10, 2015 
Vassalboro â€” Try as they might, the Camden Hills and Mount View high school golf teams could not win state titles or, for that matter, break into the top thee in their respective classes at the championships at the Natanis Golf Course. 
However, the Windjammers and Mustangs can be satisfied with being one of the coveted qualifiers and getting the experience of playing in the state tournament. 
In Class A, Thornton Academy of Saco 310 (four-golfer, 18-hole score), Cheverus of Portland 324 and Scarborough 326 were the top teams. Camden Hills tied for eighth among 11 teams at 343. 
In Class B, Cape Elizabeth 322, Old Town 334 and Maine Central Institute of Pittsfield 347 were the top teams. Mount View finished 10th among 11 teams at 380. 
In Class C, Mattanawcook Academy of Lincoln 323, St. Dominic of Auburn 329 and Winthrop 331 were the top teams. 
Class A and B golfers played 18 holes on the Tomahawk course and Class C golfers the Arrowhead layout. 
The Windjammers' individual scores were: Julian Starbird 74, Cole Anderson 75, Braden Fisher 93, Connor Russell 101 and James Orne 102. 
The Mustangs' individual scores were: Ross DeLorenzo 86 Austin Higgins 91, Joey Danna 99, Darrell Roberts 104 and Cassidy Gerrish 105. Courier Publications' sports staff can be reached by email at sports@villagesoup.com or by phone at 594-4401.
